ys. The volume showcases some of the best new work in masculinity studies. With an introduction that contextualizes the international origins of the field, Making Men, Making History is the first book to explore these themes entirely in Canadian historica settings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMasculinityzCanadaxHistory. 0aMenzCanadaxSocial conditions. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh1 aAdams, Annmarie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBienvenue, Louise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampbell, Lara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChilton, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowney, Allan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFahrni, Magda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFillion, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGossage, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGossage, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGreig, Christopher J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHudon, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJasen, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeough, Willeen G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnowles, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoch-Drake, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelcher, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNicholas, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabula